{
  "texts": [
    "I also considered three datasets involving judgments of individual words.",
    "SimLex999 (Hill et al., 2015) and Sim-Verb3500 (Gerz et al., 2016) contain judgments of similarity (as opposed to relatedness) of 999 word pairs and 3500 verb pairs, respectively.",
    "Finally, a recent dataset of iconicity judgments (the extent to which a word's form resembles its meaning) for 14,776 English words was included (Winter et al., 2023).",
    "Model I used GPT-4, a state-of-the-art large language model.",
    "The primary reason for selecting GPT-4 was its superior performance on a number of natural language processing benchmarks, as well as more general metrics of capability."
  ]
}